<?xml version="1.0" encoding="utf-8" ?>
<Defs>
            <!-- Krieger Uniform -->

    <ThingDef ParentName="GW_HOI_OnSkinBase">
        <defName>GW_HOI_DM_KriegUniform</defName>
        <label>Krieg uniform</label>
	<description>Standard dark gray fatigues of the Death Korps of Krieg. It is impregnated with chemicals to protect against biological and chemical warfare, which also gives the uniform a strong, unpleasant smell. \n\nThe rulers of Krieg once attempted to break away from the Imperium, only to be defeated by a global nuclear bombardment and a 500-year civil war to reclaim the planet. Ever since then, the Death Korps of Krieg has felt that they needed to atone for their sin of rebellion, throwing themselves into battle without heed of casualties.</description>
        <recipeMaker>
            <researchPrerequisite>GW_AM_DeathKorpsOfKrieg</researchPrerequisite>
        </recipeMaker>
        <graphicData>
            <texPath>Apparel/Guard/DKoK_GuardOnskin</texPath>
        </graphicData>
        <costStuffCount>85</costStuffCount>
        <stuffCategories>
			<li>Fabric</li>
		</stuffCategories>
        <statBases>
            <MaxHitPoints>150</MaxHitPoints>
            <Mass>1.0</Mass>
            <WorkToMake>8000</WorkToMake>
            <StuffEffectMultiplierArmor>0.3</StuffEffectMultiplierArmor>
            <StuffEffectMultiplierInsulation_Cold>0.2</StuffEffectMultiplierInsulation_Cold>
            <StuffEffectMultiplierInsulation_Heat>0.1</StuffEffectMultiplierInsulation_Heat>
            <MarketValue>150</MarketValue>
        </statBases>
        <apparel>
            <wornGraphicPath>Apparel/Guard/Onskin/DKoK_GuardOnskin</wornGraphicPath>
            <tags>
                <li>40kDeathKorps</li>
                <li>40kDeathKorpsUniform</li>
            </tags>
        </apparel>
    </ThingDef>

                <!-- Krieger Officer Uniform -->

    <ThingDef ParentName="GW_HOI_OnSkinBase">
        <defName>GW_HOI_DM_KriegOfficerUniform</defName>
        <label>Krieg officer greatcoat</label>
	<description>A greatcoat worn by Officers of the Death Korps of Krieg. The blighted world of Krieg has no aristocracy, meaning officers are selected from the rank-and-file who have survived numerous campaigns. These battle-hardened veterans have been so thoroughly stripped of their humanity that they will often refer to themselves with numbers rather than names.</description>
        <recipeMaker>
            <researchPrerequisite>GW_AM_DeathKorpsOfKrieg</researchPrerequisite>
        </recipeMaker>
        <graphicData>
            <texPath>Apparel/Officer/DKoK_OfficerOnskin</texPath>
        </graphicData>
        <costStuffCount>95</costStuffCount>
        <stuffCategories>
			<li>Fabric</li>
		</stuffCategories>
        <statBases>
            <MaxHitPoints>160</MaxHitPoints>
            <Mass>1.2</Mass>
            <WorkToMake>10000</WorkToMake>
            <StuffEffectMultiplierArmor>0.3</StuffEffectMultiplierArmor>
            <StuffEffectMultiplierInsulation_Cold>0.2</StuffEffectMultiplierInsulation_Cold>
            <StuffEffectMultiplierInsulation_Heat>0.1</StuffEffectMultiplierInsulation_Heat>
            <MarketValue>180</MarketValue>
        </statBases>
        <equippedStatOffsets>
			<SocialImpact>0.05</SocialImpact>
            <SlaveSuppressionOffset MayRequire="Ludeon.Rimworld.Ideology">0.05</SlaveSuppressionOffset>
            <MentalBreakThreshold>0.025</MentalBreakThreshold>
		</equippedStatOffsets>
        <apparel>
            <wornGraphicPath>Apparel/Officer/Onskin/DKoK_OfficerOnskin</wornGraphicPath>
            <tags>
                <li>40kDeathKorpsUniform</li>
                <li>40kGuardOfficerUniform</li>
            </tags>
        </apparel>
    </ThingDef>

	<!-- Commissar Uniform -->

    <ThingDef ParentName="GW_HOI_OnSkinBase">
        <defName>GW_HOI_DM_CommissarUniform</defName>
        <label>Krieg commissar greatcoat</label>
	<description>A greatcoat and gorget marking a commissar's rank within the Death Korps of Krieg. Commissars are trained and supplied by the Departmento Munitorium and are thus the only offworlders permitted to act within the Death Korp's forces. </description>
       <recipeMaker>
            <researchPrerequisite>GW_AM_OfficersOfAM</researchPrerequisite>
        </recipeMaker>
        <graphicData>
            <texPath>Apparel/Commissar/DKoK_CommissarOnskin</texPath>
        </graphicData>
        <costStuffCount>90</costStuffCount>
        <stuffCategories>
			<li>Fabric</li>
		</stuffCategories>
        <statBases>
            <MaxHitPoints>155</MaxHitPoints>
            <Mass>1.1</Mass>
            <WorkToMake>10000</WorkToMake>
            <StuffEffectMultiplierArmor>0.3</StuffEffectMultiplierArmor>
            <StuffEffectMultiplierInsulation_Cold>0.2</StuffEffectMultiplierInsulation_Cold>
            <StuffEffectMultiplierInsulation_Heat>0.1</StuffEffectMultiplierInsulation_Heat>
            <MarketValue>200</MarketValue>
        </statBases>
         <equippedStatOffsets>
			<SocialImpact>0.05</SocialImpact>
            <SlaveSuppressionOffset MayRequire="Ludeon.Rimworld.Ideology">0.05</SlaveSuppressionOffset>
            <MentalBreakThreshold>0.05</MentalBreakThreshold>
		</equippedStatOffsets>
        <apparel>
            <wornGraphicPath>Apparel/Commissar/Onskin/DKoK_CommissarOnskin</wornGraphicPath>
            <tags>
                <li>40kCommissar</li>
                <li>40kCommissarOnSkin</li>
            </tags>
        </apparel>
    </ThingDef>

</Defs>
